@AlamoVampire a sign that reads like this from me  

ok starlink satilites that are OPERATIONAL are not pollutants theya re just normal satilites that are a lot more volumeous than normal satilites Starlink is not the only mega constellation there is Kuiper and One Webb ect 

the tension rods on the starlink V1.5 missions are the only main space pollutants the tension rods for the V2 sats are attached to the second stage for deorbit. When starship starts to launch full size V2's in a few months there will be NO space pollutants

the launches themselves are not to bad they account for less than 1 percent of the carbon output train and cars and airplanes cause more pollution than SpaceX

I dont get where your argument is coming from 

also space shuttle launched 135 times with 2 failures. 98.51% failure rate 

falcon 9 with 253 times to date with 2 failures   99.20% failure rate 

Starship with 1 flight and 1 failure with a 100% failure rate at PRESENT with another launch this month that will probably make it to staging

soo yeah i dont get what you mean by spacex being a polluter they literally work with the FAA to MITAGATE enviromental harm

Soory for the long post
